   For AppleScript operations: need UUID

## Note on URL Scheme vs AppleScript

The Things URL scheme accepts project/area names directly. However:
- For `tasks create`: URL scheme, so names work directly
- For `tasks update --project/--area`: Uses AppleScript which requires UUIDs
- For `projects create --area`: URL scheme, so names work directly

This means resolution is mainly needed for the AppleScript-based move operations in `tasks update`.

## Edge Cases

- Name that looks like a UUID (unlikely but possible)
- Project and area with same name (resolve to correct type based on flag)
- Non-existent name â†’ clear error message
- Multiple projects with same name â†’ error or warning
